Maxim Integrated DS3231 RTC Signal Dumps
========================================

The DS3231 is a highly accurate I2C real-time clock with integrated
crystal oscillator and temperature compensation.

Device Features:
----------------
- I2C interface (address 0x68)
- ±2ppm accuracy from 0°C to +40°C
- Battery backup capability
- Two programmable alarms
- 32kHz output
- Temperature sensor (-40°C to +85°C)
- Automatic leap year compensation

Files:
------
- ds3231_ex1.sr: Complete setup and configuration sequence
- ds3231_ex2.sr: Alarm handling and status operations  
- ds3231_ex3.sr: Temperature sensor reading

Register Map (Key Registers):
-----------------------------
- 0x00-0x06: Time/Date registers (seconds, minutes, hours, day, date, month, year)
- 0x07-0x0A: Alarm 1 registers
- 0x0B-0x0D: Alarm 2 registers
- 0x0E: Control register
- 0x0F: Control/Status register
- 0x10: Aging offset register
- 0x11-0x12: Temperature registers (MSB/LSB)

Logic Analyzer Setup:
---------------------
- Device: Geeetech Mini Board Cypress FX2(LP) with fx2lafw firmware
- Sample rate: 4 MHz
- Probe 0: SCL (clock)
- Probe 1: SDA (data)

ds3231_ex1.sr - Complete Configuration:
---------------------------------------
Demonstrates full RTC setup sequence:
- Read Control register
- Write Control register (disable alarms)
- Read Control/Status register  
- Write Control/Status register (clear alarm flags)
- Write Alarm 1 registers (set alarm for 1st of month)
- Write Alarm 2 registers (set alarm every minute)
- Read current date/time
- Read temperature (MSB)
- 24-hour mode configuration

ds3231_ex2.sr - Alarm Handling:
-------------------------------
Shows alarm processing after Alarm 2 triggered:
- Read Control/Status register (check alarm flags)
- Write Control/Status register (clear alarm flag)
- Read current date/time
- Read temperature (MSB)
- Demonstrates alarm interrupt handling

ds3231_ex3.sr - Temperature Reading:
------------------------------------
Focuses on temperature sensor functionality:
- Read temperature registers (0x11-0x12)
- Temperature resolution: 0.25°C
- Two's complement format
- MSB contains integer temperature
- LSB bits 7-6 contain fractional part

Temperature Calculation:
------------------------
Temperature = MSB + (LSB >> 6) × 0.25°C
Example: MSB=0x19, LSB=0x40 → 25 + 1×0.25 = 25.25°C

For more information:
---------------------
- DS3231 datasheet: https://datasheets.maximintegrated.com/en/ds/DS3231.pdf
- I2C protocol specification
- Real-time clock applications and battery backup considerations
